M|vercel-composition-patterns|A structured repository for React composition patterns that scale. These
M|vercel-composition-patterns|patterns help avoid boolean prop proliferation by using compound components,
M|vercel-composition-patterns|lifting state, and composing internals.
M|vercel-composition-patterns|- `rules/` - Individual rule files (one per rule)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|- `_sections.md` - Section metadata (titles, impacts, descriptions)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|- `_template.md` - Template for creating new rules
M|vercel-composition-patterns|- `area-description.md` - Individual rule files
M|vercel-composition-patterns|- `metadata.json` - doc metadata (version, organization, abstract)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|- **`AGENTS.md`** - Compiled output (generated)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|- `architecture-avoid-boolean-props.md` - Don't add boolean props to customize
M|vercel-composition-patterns|behavior
M|vercel-composition-patterns|- `architecture-compound-components.md` - Structure as compound components with
M|vercel-composition-patterns|shared ctx
M|vercel-composition-patterns|- `state-lift-state.md` - Lift state into provider components
M|vercel-composition-patterns|- `state-ctx-interface.md` - Define clear ctx interfaces
M|vercel-composition-patterns|(state/actions/meta)
M|vercel-composition-patterns|- `state-decouple-implementation.md` - Decouple state management from UI
M|vercel-composition-patterns|- `patterns-children-over-render-props.md` - Prefer children over renderX props
M|vercel-composition-patterns|- `patterns-explicit-variants.md` - Create explicit component variants
M|vercel-composition-patterns|1. **Composition over cfg** — Instead of adding props, let consumers
M|vercel-composition-patterns|compose
M|vercel-composition-patterns|2. **Lift your state** — State in providers, not trapped in components
M|vercel-composition-patterns|3. **Compose your internals** — Subcomponents access ctx, not props
M|vercel-composition-patterns|4. **Explicit variants** — Create ThreadComposer, EditComposer, not Composer
M|vercel-composition-patterns|with isThread
M|vercel-composition-patterns|1. Copy `rules/_template.md` to `rules/area-description.md`
M|vercel-composition-patterns|2. Choose the appropriate area prefix:
M|vercel-composition-patterns|- `architecture-` for Component Architecture
M|vercel-composition-patterns|- `state-` for State Management
M|vercel-composition-patterns|- `patterns-` for Implementation Patterns
M|vercel-composition-patterns|3. Fill in the frontmatter and cnt
M|vercel-composition-patterns|4. Ensure you have clear examples with explanations
M|vercel-composition-patterns|- `CRITICAL` - Foundational patterns, prevents unmaintainable code
M|vercel-composition-patterns|- `HIGH` - Significant maintainability improvements
